CA Climate Zone (1-16)
Code Reference
BldgType - building type descriptor to differentiate single family, multifamily and potentially other types  (Proj:BldgTypeTblStr = 'SingleFam' or 'MultiFam')
WHFan - (0/1) whole house fans required in standard design
WHFcfmpersf - cfm per floor area delivered  by whole house fan
WHFWperCFM - whole house default/standard design fan power (W/CFM)
WHFatticrelief - ft2 per cfm
WHFcfmdivisor - used to reduce effective cfm
PVRate - kTDV/kWdc credit for photovoltaic systems
column10: (0 value indicates CZ's w/ NO available PV credit)

column4: PVMax - Maximum percent cooling energy credit for PV (varies for SFam & MFam models)
column16: SAC 6/5/17 - consolidated sf & mf columns into 1

column4: GridHarmCredPk - peak grid harmonization credit TDV as a fraction of Standard Design TDV
SummerPkFirstHr - First hour of the summer peak TDV period (18 => hour between 5p & 6p)
column16: SAC 12/17/17 - added to enable TOU battery control (tic #941)

column4: CFMperTon -  min. cooling airflow rate required
VerifyCharge - binary flag for required refrigerant charge verification
WperCFM - max. fan watt draw allowed (for systems other than gas furnace air handlers)
GFurnWperCFM - max. fan watt draw allowed for Gas Furnace Air Handlers

column4: SDHVWperCFM - max. fan watt draw allowed for small duct high velocity forced air system

column4: ACH50 - default building leakage rate assumed  (varies for SFam & MFam models)
column16: SAC 6/5/17 - consolidated sf & mf columns into 1

column4: wsf - weather and shielding factor used to calculate Qinf (effective ann avg infiltration rate (cfm))
column16: SAC 4/11/17 - added for 2019 minimum IAQ ventilation calcs

column4: wsfStationName - name of weather station where weather and shielding factor is being used
DuctRval - Prescriptive reqs for duct insulation Rvalue
AltDuctRval - Prescriptive reqs for ALTERED duct insulation Rvalue
DuctLkg - max duct leakage rate
exDuctLkg - max existing duct leakage rate
WallUval - Prescriptive max for ext wall Uvalue
AltUfactor - Max Window Ufactor for Alterations
AltSHGC - Max Window SHGC for Alterations
AltSkyUfactor - Max Skylight Ufactor for Alterations
AltSkySHGC - Max Skylight SHGC for Alterations
CeilIns - CavityLayer insulation of CeilingBelowAttic
FloorIns - Cavity Layer insulation of ExtFloor and FloorOverCrawl - Raised Floor
ConcFloorIns - Cavity Layer insulation of ExtFloor and FloorOverCrawl - Concrete Raised
SlabEdgeIns - Insulation R-value  and depth (concatenated) of slab floor edge
HtSlabEdgeIns - Insulation R-value  and depth (concatenated) of heated slab floor edge
StdICQEnclCavInsMult - 'Standard' (vs. Improved) insulation construction quality enclosed cavity insulation R-value multiplier
StdInsulConsQuality - insulation construction quality setting for Standard design model
WindowUfactor - Prescriptive reqs for window Ufactor
Window SHGC- Prescriptive reqs for window SHGC
Window Percentage - Above this value the window area is fixed in standard design
DoorUfactor - Prescriptive reqs for exterior & interior demising door Ufactor
RadiantBarrier - Prescriptive reqs for radiant barrier
SteepRoofReflect - Prescriptive reqs for steep roof reflectivity
FlatRoofReflect - Prescriptive reqs for flat roof reflectivity
RoofAboveDeckIns - presriptive reqs for above deck insulation
AltLowRoofRiseAboveDeckIns - presriptive reqs for Altered, LowRoofRise (< 2:12) roof above deck insulation
RoofBelowDeckIns - prescriptive reqs for below deck insulation  - added KN 03/17/2015
column19: SAC 6/5/17 - consolidated sf & mf columns into 1

column4: RoofCavInsOverFrm - whether or not thick Cavity insulation of Attic Roof constructions cover roof framing
column19: SAC 6/5/17 - consolidated sf & mf columns into 1

column4: StdFrameExtWallCons - construction used to model std design framed walls
StdFrameIntWallCons - construction used to model std design interior framed walls
StdMassExtWallCons - construction used to model std design exterior mass walls
StdMassUndWallCons - construction used to model std design underground mass walls
StdCeilCons - construction used to model std design ceilings below attics
StdRoofCons - construction used to model std design roofs
StdFrameExtFloorCons - construction used to model std design framed floors
StdConcExtFloorCons - construction used to model std design concrete floors
StdFlrOvrCrawlCons - construction used to model std design floor over crawlspace
StdConcFlrOvrCrawlCons - construction used to model std design concrete floors over crawlspace
StdFrameIntFloorCons - construction used to model std design interior floor
NetSurpComp (kBtu/kWh) - Net Surplus Compensation (NSC) small PV generation TDV benefit for all kWh generated above PV cap
MinZNETier - Minimum tier for models being classified as zero net energy (ZNE)
column19: SAC 6/5/17 - consolidated sf & mf columns into 1

column4: HPWHLocWhenNoGarage - Std design HPWH location when model includes no attached Garage (code vints >= 2019)
DHWCompactDistrib - applicable only to code vintages >= 2019 - compact distribution option for central and non-electric DHW systems
ElecDHWCompactDistrib - applicable only to code vintages >= 2019 - compact distribution option for non-central, all-electric DHW systems
DHWDwellUnitDist - Dwelling unit DHW distribution type
ElecDHWDwellUnitDist - Dwelling unit DHW distribution type for non-central, all-electric systems
ElecDHWWIndowUfactor - Window Ufactor to be used for models where HPWHs used for std design water heating
ElecDHWDrnWtrHtRecovEff - Drain water heat recovery efficiency (currently used just for 2019 std design HPWH models)
ElecDHWDrnWtrHtRecovShwrSrvd - Drain water heat recovery percent showers served
ElecDHWDrnWtrHtRecovConfig - Drain water heat recovery configuration
ElecDHWCompactFactor - compact distribution compactness factor
